  <title>Help for Administration of Election.aspx Page</title>
  <link href="/Admin/Help/Help.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" />
</head>
<body>
  The links in the Election Report at the bottom allow you to perform the primary
  functions of this form, namely:
  <ul>
    <li>add, change or delete candidate biographical information, picture and responses
      to issue questions (only available to certain users)</li>
    <li>add, change or delete candidates in the election </li>
    <li>add, chage or delete office contests in the election</li>
  </ul>
  The other four sections preceeding the election report allow you to perform other
  less frequent funtions, as described in each section.<br />
  <strong>Links on the Election Report<br />
  </strong>Every office contest in the election has 1) an office contest link, 2)links
  for each candidate to a form where a picture, biographical information, and the
  positions and views of the candidate can be entered, 3) links for each candidte
  to a form where the candidates ballot information can be edited, and 4) links to
  candidates' websites and email addresses, where avilable.<br />
  <br />
  <strong>Office Contest Information:</strong> Clicking on the office title link will
  present a form where you can edit the office contest on ballots including changing:
  <ul>
    <li>the office title</li>
    <li>(vote for no more than x)</li>
    <li>write in instructions</li>
    <li>number of write in lines to provide</li>
    <li>office positions</li>
    <li>whether the candidte has a running mate</li>
  </ul>
  The form will also allow you to:
  <ul>
    <li>add and delelete candidates</li>
    <li>change candidate names on ballots</li>
  </ul>
  <strong>Candidate Pictures and Biographical Information: </strong>Certain users
  are permitted to enter information about candidates that is obtained from the candidates'
  websites. These users will find a cadidate picture (or No Photo) image link in the
  report. Clicking this link will present the same form the candidate uses to enter
  biographical information and a picture about him or herself, including candidate's:
  <ul>
    <li>name as it should appear on ballots</li>
    <li>political party</li>
    <li>website, email, postal address and phone</li>
    <li>picture</li>
    <li>biographical information, including
      <ul>
        <li>general statement</li>
        <li>personal information</li>
        <li>education</li>
        <li>professional</li>
        <li>military</li>
        <li>civic</li>
        <li>political</li>
        <li>religion</li>
        <li>accomplishments</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
  </ul>
  <strong>Candidate Ballot Information: </strong>Clicking the candidate name link
  will present a form where you can:
  <ul>
    <li>remove the candiate from the office contest</li>
    <li>indicate whether the candiate is the incumbent</li>
    <li>change the order presented on ballots</li>
    <li>add, change or delete candiate information, including:
    <ul>
      <li>name as it should appear on ballots</li>
      <li>political party</li>
      <li>website, email, postal address and phone</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  </ul>
  <strong>Candidate Websites and Email Addresses: </strong>In the rightmost column
  of the report are the website and email addresses we have. The website address are
  useful to certain users who are permitted to enter information obtained from the
  candidates' websites.
</body>
